window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>I've never hated anyone as much as I hate him.</b></p> <p>The day my sister died, I told her best friend I never wanted to see him again, and I meant it. I lost her because of him. Everything I used to care about means nothing now because of him.</p> <p>It's all because of him.</p> <p>So when he shows up on my driveway two years later and tells me he's moving in with me for his freshman year of college, I kick his ass and tell him to disappear. For good this time.</p> <p>But I already know the defiant little brat's not gonna listen. He never does.</p> <p>Being near him again makes me crazy. I'm supposed to be the college basketball star my father raised me to be, but now I'm focused on a new game. I'm obsessed with watching him, touching him, breaking him. His body, his head, his heart, anything I can get my hands on…</p> <p>I'm gonna take it all until he's got nothing left.</p> <p>And even though he knows exactly what I'm doing to him, he's gonna let me do it anyway.</p>"; 
